File: South African comedian Trevor Noah has been nominated for a Grammy. NEW YORK - Local comedian turned international star Trevor Noah has received another opportunity for greatness on Wednesday. The comedy darling has been nominated for a Grammy award in the category of Best Comedy Album. READ: Trevor Noah makes history at sold-out Madison Square Garden Noah is nominated with American comedians, Ellen DeGeneres, Jim Gaffigan, Aziz Ansari, and Dave Chapelle. Last year, Noah presented an award at the 2018 Grammys in New York. The awards will be hosted by multiple Grammy winner Alicia Keys on 25 January 2020.